When building the ML model to predict photovoltaic performance of PSCs including Jsc, Voc, FF and PCE, three parameters are used as input parameters: i) the band gap (Eg) of OMHP material, ii) the energy difference (ΔH) between the HOMO of HTL and OMHP material, iii) the energy difference (ΔL) between the LUMO of ETL and OMHP material. The schematic energy band diagrams of n–i–p and p–i–n structures are presented in Fig. 1. For n–i–p or p–i–n, ΔH and ΔL are both calculated by ΔH=HTLHOMO−OMHPHOMO\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
